due.title: Lab: Waves - Diffraction Patterns
due.description:
Access the PhET Waves simulation below:
https://phet.colorado.edu/sims/html/wave-interference/latest/wave-interference_en.html

You will be observing the pattern (brightness band) on a screen caused by light diffraction and interference through one or two slits. Choose only ONE of the following to do: single OR double slit patterns.

I. Single slit patterns:

Click on Slits (make sure slits is set to one)

Set the Amplitude to Max

Underneath Amplitude slider, select the laser option on the right

Click the checkbox for screen and also for graph

Set slit width to 900 nm (nanometers) and place the single slit (beige/yellow) barrier approximately in the middle.

How does changing the frequency affect the width of the brightness band on the screen?

Set frequency to Violet and slit width to 900nm

How does moving the slit (beige/yellow) barrier further from the screen affect the width of the brightness band on the screen?

Does this confirm the single slit equation? 
	x = λL/w 
where x is the width of the brightness band, λ is the wavelength of light, L is the distance of the barrier/slit from the screen and w is the width of the slit
